  "description": [
    "THE BROWNING CHIEF John E Davies Editor and Owner A weekly newspaper published every Friday at Browning Glacier County Montana Entered as 2nd class matter July IS 1931 at the postoffice at Browning Montana under act of March 3 1879 Subscription 200 year in advance PROGRAM FOR KOREA There has been great encour agement in the fact that mem bers of the United Nations have specific plans for what should be done not merely in Korea nor to Korea but for Korea To often victorious armies have suddenly finished off a war only to discover that no clear conclusive thinking has been done as to what ought to be the results of the victory In this case not only one nation but a number of nations have plans and fortunately these plans advanced by the United States Great Britain Canada and others have great similiar ity throughout One point in substance they all start with There must be a unified and independent Korea This is in keeping with the UN General Assemblys resolution in 1948 which recognized the Re public of Korea as the only legal government in the area The next point of importance though not in the order"
  ],
